  <title>Drag&amp;Drop</title>
  <conbody>
    <p id="drag-drop-intro">You can move an element, its content or any document portion to another location. Drag&amp;drop<indexterm>drag&amp;drop</indexterm> editing is available in the <xref href="content-map.xml">ContentMap</xref>, in the <xref href="editing-window.xml">Editing Window</xref>, and between them.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p><xref href="drag-drop-selected-content.xml">
            <b>Drag&amp;drop selected content</b>
          </xref></p>
        <p conref="drag-drop-selected-content.xml#drag-drop-selected-content/drag-drop-selected-content"/>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><xref href="drag-drop-without-selection.xml">
            <b>Drag&amp;drop without selection</b>
          </xref></p>
        <p conref="drag-drop-without-selection.xml#drag-drop-without-selection/drag-drop-without-selection"/>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><xref href="copy-paste-by-using-drag-drop.xml">
            <b>Copy&amp;paste by using drag&amp;drop</b>
          </xref></p>
        <p conref="copy-paste-by-using-drag-drop.xml#copypaste-by-using-dragdrop/copy-paste-by-drag-drop-intro"/>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </conbody>
</concept>
